'''Mefu Shrine''' (めふじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} located in {{ill|lt=Shimane Prefecture|Q132751|qid=Q132751|1=Shimane Prefecture}}, {{ill|lt=Matsue City|Q207321|qid=Q207321|1=Matsue}}. It is a Shikinaisha, and under the {{ill|lt=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|Q712534|qid=Q712534|lt=former shrine ranking system|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}} it was designated as a prefectural shrine. It is the sixth site of the {{ill|lt=Izumo Province Sacred Sites of Shinto and Buddhism|Q11395860|qid=Q11395860|1=Izumo Shinbutsu Pilgrimage}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
The principal deity is {{ill|lt=Hayaakitsumiko / Hayaakitsuhime|Q11326733|qid=Q11326733|lt=Hayakitsuhime-no-Kami|1=Hayakitsuhiko and Hayakitsuhime}}, with {{ill|qid=Q10881556|lt=Isotakeru-no-Kami|Q10881556|qid=Q10881556|qid=Q10881556|lt=Isotakeru-no-Mikoto|1=Isotakeru-no-Mikoto}} and {{ill|lt=Ooyatsuhime / Tsumatsuhime|Q10935047|qid=Q10935047|lt=Ooyatsuhime-no-Mikoto and Tsumatsuhime-no-Mikoto|1=Oyatsuhime and Tsumatsuhime}} enshrined together as associate deities.

=== History ===
It appears in the '{{ill|lt=Izumo-no-Kuni Fudoki|Q11395858|qid=Q11395858|1=Izumo no Kuni Fudoki}}' as “Mefu no Yashiro” (賣布社), and in the '{{ill|lt=Engishiki|Q1342448|qid=Q1342448|1=Engishiki}}' as “Mefu Jinja” (賣布神社). It is said that the shrine was originally located on the western shore of the Irie of Ōi ({{ill|lt=Lake Shinji|Q1151248|qid=Q1151248|1=Lake Shinji}}). Due to tidal currents and changes in topography, it was relocated eastward multiple times, and around the {{ill|lt=13th century|Q7049|qid=Q7049|1=13th century}} it came to be enshrined at its present location. There was also a period when it was known as Shirakata Daimyōjin or Hashihime Daimyōjin.

=== Subsidiary shrines within the precincts ===
* Wadatatsumi Shrine
* Kotohira Shrine
* Funadama Shrine
* Ebisu Shrine
* Dōsojin Shrine
* Shirakata Tojin Arakami
* Jōkō Shrine
* Ōmatsu Arakami

=== Festivals ===
* January 8: Shiokai-sai
* July 12: Funamiyuki Shinto rite
* October 9: Takibi Shinto rite
* October 10: {{ill|lt=Annual festival|Q11385469|qid=Q11385469|1=Reisai}}, Gokyō-sai (Suzuki Festival)

=== Surroundings ===
Located in the urban area of Matsue City. The {{ill|lt=Ōhashi River|Q11436587|qid=Q11436587|1=Ōhashi River}} flows to the north of the shrine, and the Matsue Shin-Ōhashi Bridge connects it to the northern bank.

=== Access ===
* Approximately 500 meters northwest from {{ill|lt=Matsue Station|Q1058652|qid=Q1058652|1=Matsue Station}} on {{ill|lt=West Japan Railway Company|Q502125|qid=Q502125|1=West Japan Railway Company}} (JR West).

